11:58.092 --> 11:59.635
left us!

11:59.718 --> 12:02.513
- Oh, gosh.
I'm so sorry.

12:02.596 --> 12:04.640
- My dad tells me
I'm just like her,

12:04.723 --> 12:06.517
so I thought the locket
would be a perfect thing

12:06.600 --> 12:08.477
to put in the time capsule.

12:08.561 --> 12:10.271
But...
- But what?

12:10.354 --> 12:12.481
- I--I just can't.

12:12.565 --> 12:14.316
It's all I have left of her!

12:14.400 --> 12:15.568
- It's OK. It's OK.

12:15.651 --> 12:16.986
- I'm so sorry!
- I understand. No.

12:17.069 --> 12:19.155
Look, you obviously gave the
assignment a lot of thought,

12:19.238 --> 12:20.906
and that's
the important thing.

12:20.990 --> 12:22.283
- Really?
- Of course.

12:22.366 --> 12:23.659
Of course. And don't worry.

12:23.742 --> 12:27.329
I'm gonna give you full credit
for the assignment.

12:27.413 --> 12:30.249
- Thank you so much.

12:30.332 --> 12:33.794
<i>[tender vocalizing]</i>

12:33.878 --> 12:35.629
<i>[music stops]</i>

12:35.713 --> 12:37.173
Acting.

12:37.256 --> 12:38.674
<i>[upbeat vocalizing]</i>

12:38.757 --> 12:40.634
- All right,
let's bury this puppy.

12:40.718 --> 12:49.393
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:54.023 --> 12:55.357
- So I guess you won't know
what Zoey thinks about you

12:55.441 --> 12:59.737
for another 20 years.

12:59.820 --> 13:01.030
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:01.113 --> 13:04.492
<i>MAN: ♪ Ah, ah ♪</i>

13:07.286 --> 13:09.538
[thunder crashing]

13:09.622 --> 13:12.583
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

13:12.666 --> 13:20.716
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:23.177 --> 13:25.554
<i>LOGAN: So I guess you won't</i>
<i>know what Zoey thinks about you</i>

13:25.638 --> 13:28.349
<i>for another 20 years.</i>

13:28.432 --> 13:30.142
[thunder crashes]

13:30.226 --> 13:33.771
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:33.854 --> 13:35.731
- Finally!

13:35.814 --> 13:38.275
I get to watch it.

13:38.359 --> 13:41.320
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:41.403 --> 13:42.613
Player on.

13:43.572 --> 13:45.950
<i>COMPUTER: Hello, Chase.</i>

13:46.033 --> 13:50.412
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:50.496 --> 13:53.165
<i>Old-style DVD detected.</i>

13:53.249 --> 13:54.959
<i>Choose display format.</i>

13:55.042 --> 13:56.460
- Hologram.
[electronic beep]

13:56.544 --> 13:59.088
<i>COMPUTER: Image playback.</i>

13:59.171 --> 14:06.011
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:06.095 --> 14:08.639
<i>- There are so many things</i>
<i>I can say about Chase.</i>

14:08.722 --> 14:10.474
<i>For one thing,</i>
<i>he's the first person</i>

14:10.558 --> 14:12.142
<i>I ever met here at PCA,</i>

14:12.226 --> 14:14.812
<i>and we've gotten to be</i>
<i>really close friends.</i>

14:14.895 --> 14:17.439
<i>But there is something</i>
<i>I've never told Chase,</i>

14:17.523 --> 14:19.108
<i>and that is...</i>

14:19.191 --> 14:20.609
- That is what?

14:20.693 --> 14:21.902
<i>MICHAEL: Chase...</i>

14:21.986 --> 14:22.861
- Zoey!

14:22.945 --> 14:23.862
Zoey, come back!

14:23.946 --> 14:24.989
<i>MICHAEL: Chase!</i>

14:25.072 --> 14:26.615
- Say it! Say it!

14:26.699 --> 14:28.325
Say it! Say it!

14:28.409 --> 14:29.994
Zoey, come back!

14:30.077 --> 14:31.120
- Chase!

14:31.203 --> 14:33.372
[bang]
- Aah!

14:33.455 --> 14:34.957
Michael!

14:35.040 --> 14:36.667
Man, you wrecked my dream!

14:36.750 --> 14:38.836
I was just about to hear what
Zoey said about me on her DVD!

14:38.919 --> 14:40.546
Man, why'd you wake me up?

14:40.629 --> 14:42.590
- I just wanted to know
if you had an extra pillow

14:42.673 --> 14:43.716
I could borrow.

14:46.594 --> 14:47.511
- Here!

14:47.595 --> 14:49.680
Now let me get back
to my dream!

14:53.309 --> 14:56.562
[thunder crashing]

14:56.645 --> 14:57.855
Am I asleep yet?

14:57.938 --> 14:58.939
- Nope.

15:00.232 --> 15:01.817
- Come with me!
- Where?

15:01.900 --> 15:03.235
- We gotta dig up
that time capsule.

15:03.319 --> 15:05.154
- Man, it is 2:00
in the mornin'!

15:05.237 --> 15:06.780
- I have got to know
what Zoey said about me!

15:06.864 --> 15:08.115
I need your help!

15:08.198 --> 15:09.158
- Are you insane?

15:09.241 --> 15:10.576
I don't--aah!

15:11.952 --> 15:14.872
[both grunting]

15:14.955 --> 15:19.126
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:19.209 --> 15:20.336
You're insane!

15:20.419 --> 15:21.837
- Just keep digging!

15:21.920 --> 15:23.005
- What do you think
I'm doin',

15:23.088 --> 15:24.632
having a shrimp cocktail?

15:24.715 --> 15:26.675
I tell you, man, out
of all the crazy things that--

15:26.759 --> 15:28.719
[metallic clang]
- Ahh! There it is!

15:28.802 --> 15:31.263
Come on, help me get the dirt
out of the way!

15:31.347 --> 15:33.432
<i>[dramatic rock music]</i>

15:33.515 --> 15:34.850
Dig! Come on, man, dig!

15:34.933 --> 15:36.352
- I'm trying.
It's wet.

15:37.645 --> 15:38.687
- You got it?

15:38.771 --> 15:39.813
- I got it! You got it?

15:39.897 --> 15:41.357
- I got it!

15:41.440 --> 15:48.030
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:48.113 --> 15:49.948
Finally, I got it!

15:50.032 --> 15:52.034
I got it!

15:52.117 --> 15:55.204
[thunder crashing]

15:55.287 --> 15:57.289
Come on, man.
Help me rebury the time capsule

15:57.373 --> 15:58.624
so no one knows we dug it up.

15:58.707 --> 16:00.334
- Sure. I mean,

16:00.417 --> 16:03.128
what else do I have to do
at 3:00 in the morning?

16:03.212 --> 16:05.130
[thunder crashing]

16:05.214 --> 16:08.175
[both grunting]

16:08.258 --> 16:14.306
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:14.390 --> 16:16.475
- Quinn,
let's just face it.

16:16.558 --> 16:19.561
Nothing's gonna stop
your freakish snoring.

16:19.645 --> 16:21.980
- Don't give up yet.

16:22.064 --> 16:25.484
- [groans]
We've tried everything.

16:25.567 --> 16:27.986
- No,

16:28.070 --> 16:31.073
we haven't tried these.

16:31.156 --> 16:33.617
<i>[relaxed music]</i>

16:33.701 --> 16:35.577
- Eww! What are those?

16:35.661 --> 16:39.081
- A very rare breed
of guppies from South Africa.

16:39.164 --> 16:42.126
- OK, and how
are South African guppies

16:42.209 --> 16:43.836
gonna stop you from snoring?

16:43.919 --> 16:45.421
- Well, when you
remove them from water,

16:45.504 --> 16:47.005
they secrete a sticky liquid

16:47.089 --> 16:49.591
that's supposed to numb
the mucus membranes of humans.

16:49.675 --> 16:50.926
- And?

16:51.009 --> 16:52.261
- If I stick these
up my nose,

16:52.344 --> 16:53.637
they'll coat my inner nostrils,

16:53.721 --> 16:56.724
and the numbing effect
should stop my snoring.

16:56.807 --> 16:57.766
- I'm going away now.

16:57.850 --> 16:59.351
- Oh, no, no, no, no.

16:59.435 --> 17:01.103
I need you to stay here
and watch me sleep

17:01.186 --> 17:03.105
and tell me if it works.

17:03.188 --> 17:03.480
Ready?

17:03.564 --> 17:05.773
- Nooo.

17:05.858 --> 17:08.318
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:08.402 --> 17:09.987
[Quinn sniffing]

17:10.069 --> 17:18.746
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:18.829 --> 17:22.624
This is the most disturbing
moment of my life.

17:22.708 --> 17:25.085
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:25.169 --> 17:28.213
<i>[dramatic instrumental music]</i>

17:28.297 --> 17:36.722
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:46.982 --> 17:48.734
<i>- Hi. I'm Zoey Brooks,</i>

17:48.817 --> 17:49.902
<i>and if you're watching this,</i>

17:49.985 --> 17:51.612
<i>it must be 20 years from now.</i>

17:51.695 --> 17:54.323
<i>I bet a lot of stuff's changed</i>
<i>since I went to PCA.</i>

17:54.406 --> 17:56.200
[speaking squeakily
and indistinctly]

17:56.283 --> 17:57.993
<i>So having Nicole as my roommate</i>

17:58.076 --> 17:59.661
<i>is definitely</i>
<i>one of the best things</i>

17:59.745 --> 18:01.038
<i>about my life here at PCA.</i>

18:01.121 --> 18:02.831
<i>And now I want to tell you</i>

18:02.915 --> 18:05.584
<i>about one of the most special</i>
<i>people I've ever met.</i>

18:05.667 --> 18:07.211
<i>His name is Chase Matthews,</i>

18:07.294 --> 18:10.172
<i>and he's one of the funniest,</i>
<i>coolest, nice--</i>

18:10.255 --> 18:13.175
<i>[solemn music]</i>

18:13.258 --> 18:20.349
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:20.432 --> 18:21.391
- Michael.

18:21.475 --> 18:23.393
Dude, wake up.

18:25.521 --> 18:27.231
- Michael's asleep.

18:27.314 --> 18:29.942
Leave a message at the beep.

18:30.025 --> 18:32.528
Beep.

18:32.611 --> 18:33.654
- Come on.

18:33.737 --> 18:35.864
I gotta talk to you, man.

18:35.948 --> 18:37.282
- Aw, man, what now?

18:37.366 --> 18:39.284
You want me to go scuba divin'?

18:39.368 --> 18:40.577
- Is this wrong?

18:40.661 --> 18:42.329
- Is what wrong?

18:42.412 --> 18:45.374
- For me to watch Zoey's
DVD without her permission.

18:45.457 --> 18:46.834
Is it wrong?

18:46.917 --> 18:49.503
- Does it feel wrong?

18:49.586 --> 18:51.129
- Kinda.

18:51.213 --> 18:54.842
- Then you don't need
to ask me what you already know.

18:54.925 --> 19:02.933
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:27.457 --> 19:35.215
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:37.843 --> 19:40.596
- There they are.

19:40.679 --> 19:41.680
- Hey.

19:41.763 --> 19:43.599
You guys.

19:43.682 --> 19:45.976
Hey!

19:46.059 --> 19:48.103
- Nicole, it's morning.

19:48.186 --> 19:49.813
- Oh, hey, guys.

19:51.273 --> 19:54.192
I guess we overslept.

19:54.276 --> 19:56.320
<i>[bright instrumental music]</i>

19:56.403 --> 19:58.906
We overslept! Quinn! Wake up!

19:58.989 --> 20:00.073
Get up!
- What?

20:00.157 --> 20:01.742
- We slept
through the night!

20:01.825 --> 20:04.119
- I didn't snore?
- No! The guppies worked!

20:04.202 --> 20:05.829
- The guppies worked!
[both squealing]

20:05.913 --> 20:07.915
- Did she say guppies?
- I heard guppies.

20:07.998 --> 20:09.249
- South African guppies--

20:09.333 --> 20:09.791
she put 'em up her nose.

20:09.875 --> 20:12.878
- Yeah! See?

20:13.962 --> 20:14.922
[plop]

20:15.005 --> 20:17.090
[exhaling sharply]

20:17.174 --> 20:18.133
[plop]
- Ooh!

20:18.216 --> 20:19.259
- Look!

20:21.720 --> 20:24.181
- Yeah, those are guppies.

20:24.264 --> 20:25.474
[both chuckling]

20:25.557 --> 20:27.643
- Mm. Hey. Hey, girls.

20:27.726 --> 20:29.561
You guys catch Leno last night?

20:29.645 --> 20:30.812
GIRLS: No.

20:30.896 --> 20:33.440
- Oh, you missed a gem.

20:33.523 --> 20:35.859
He did this joke
about how slow the mail is.

20:35.943 --> 20:37.319
It killed me.

20:37.402 --> 20:39.363
He goes...he says,

20:39.446 --> 20:41.657
"The mail is so slow..."

20:41.740 --> 20:44.826
[laughing]

20:44.910 --> 20:46.787
[coughing]

20:46.870 --> 20:49.998
- You all right?

20:50.082 --> 20:50.958
ALL: No, no, no, no!
Don't drink that!

20:51.041 --> 20:54.294
- No! The guppies!

20:54.378 --> 20:55.587
- [gulps]

20:55.671 --> 20:57.297
Oh, that's better.

20:57.381 --> 20:58.548
Whoo.

21:00.842 --> 21:03.804
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

21:03.887 --> 21:05.681
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:05.764 --> 21:07.140
[horn honks]

21:07.224 --> 21:14.481
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:24.116 --> 21:29.079
<i>MAN: ♪ You were just</i>
<i>lyin' there ♪</i>

21:29.162 --> 21:33.166
<i>♪ Broken down and nowhere ♪</i>

21:33.250 --> 21:35.419
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:35.502 --> 21:36.712
- Hey.

21:38.505 --> 21:39.589
- Hello.

21:39.673 --> 21:41.049
- Whatcha doin'?

21:41.133 --> 21:42.509
- Resting.

21:42.592 --> 21:43.885
- Why?

21:43.969 --> 21:45.387
- Well, I haven't gotten
much sleep

21:45.470 --> 21:46.763
in the past couple days.

21:46.847 --> 21:48.056
- How come?

21:48.140 --> 21:49.891
- Oh, you know,
I just been busy...

21:49.975 --> 21:51.351
doin' stuff.

21:51.435 --> 21:53.395
- Yeah,
stuff can keep you busy.

21:53.478 --> 21:54.771
- Yeah.

21:54.855 --> 21:57.357
- So, listen.
- OK.

21:57.441 --> 21:59.568
- You know how you asked me
what I said about you on my DVD?

21:59.651 --> 22:00.944
- Uh-huh.

22:01.028 --> 22:02.821
- And I said
you'll find out in 20 years?

22:02.904 --> 22:04.406
- Right.

22:04.489 --> 22:06.283
- Well, I decided
that was a little mean.

22:06.366 --> 22:09.077
- You did?
- Mm-hmm.

22:09.161 --> 22:10.162
- So?

22:10.245 --> 22:11.997
- So I'm gonna tell ya.

22:12.080 --> 22:13.415
- You're gonna tell me?

22:13.498 --> 22:14.541
- Yep.

22:14.624 --> 22:16.001
In 10 years.

22:16.084 --> 22:17.002
- What?

22:17.085 --> 22:18.295
- Bye!

22:18.378 --> 22:20.213
- Oh, you're dead.

22:21.089 --> 22:23.175
- Ooh, I'm scared!

22:24.092 --> 22:25.927
- [grunts]

22:26.011 --> 22:27.471
[engine revving]
What the--

22:27.554 --> 22:29.598
OK, now you're really dead!

22:29.681 --> 22:31.850
{\an8}- Gotta catch me to kill me!

22:31.933 --> 22:33.018
{\an8}- Zoey!
[horn honks]

22:33.101 --> 22:34.394
{\an8}Zoey, wait!

22:34.478 --> 22:35.729
{\an8}Zoey?

22:35.812 --> 22:37.272
{\an8}I know where you live!

22:37.355 --> 22:38.440
{\an8}Zoey!

22:38.523 --> 22:40.025
{\an8}<i>WOMAN: ♪ Yeah, yeah, you ♪</i>

22:40.108 --> 22:45.030
{\an8}<i>♪ Just gotta let it loose ♪</i>

22:45.113 --> 22:48.325
{\an8}<i>♪ Don't walk away ♪</i>

22:48.408 --> 22:49.993
{\an8}<i>♪ Yeah, yeah ♪</i>

22:50.077 --> 22:52.037
{\an8}<i>♪ If you wanna play ♪</i>

22:52.120 --> 22:54.122
{\an8}<i>♪ Come and play today ♪</i>

22:54.206 --> 22:58.460
{\an8}<i>♪ Let's just get away, yeah ♪</i>

22:58.543 --> 23:00.128
{\an8}<i>♪ I will make you see ♪</i>

23:00.212 --> 23:02.589
{\an8}<i>♪ All of the things ♪</i>

23:02.672 --> 23:04.132
{\an8}<i>♪ That you can be ♪</i>

23:04.216 --> 23:06.718
{\an8}<i>♪ Believe in yourself ♪</i>

23:06.802 --> 23:09.888
{\an8}<i>♪ Come follow me ♪</i>

23:09.971 --> 23:11.973
{\an8}<i>♪ Yeah, yeah ♪</i>

23:12.057 --> 23:16.436
{\an8}<i>♪ Yeah ♪</i>

23:16.520 --> 23:17.521
{\an8}<i>[ding]</i>

23:17.604 --> 23:19.481
{\an8}<i>MAN: Mmm.</i>

23:19.564 --> 23:21.108
{\an8}<i>[Quinn snoring]</i>
